;; check:fcis allowlist — genuine FC/IS debt only.
;;
;; The gate (bb check:fcis) bans (throw ...) and mutable state (defonce, atom,
;; swap!, reset!, …) in core namespaces.
;;
;; Namespaces that LEGITIMATELY need an exception are exempted INLINE via
;; ^:boundary/allow-throw / ^:boundary/allow-mutable-state ns metadata, with the
;; rationale next to the code — the interceptor engine's error propagation
;; (boundary.core.interceptor, …interceptor-context), the validation-testing
;; tooling (…validation.behavior / .generators / .snapshot), and the local
;; volatile! accumulators in boundary.platform.core.search.ranking.
;;
;; This file is reserved for REAL debt to migrate. The single remaining entry is
;; a mutable rule registry (two defonce atoms) that predates the shell-per-
;; registry pattern and should move out of the functional core — tracked in
;; BOU-188. Remove it here once that move lands.
{:allow-throw
 [boundary.core.validation.registry]

 :allow-mutable-state
 [boundary.core.validation.registry]}
